President Muhammadu Buhari Wednesday approved the reappointment of Dr Hajo Sani OON, as the Senior Special Assistant to the President on Administration. He also approved the appointment of Malam Hadi Uba as Special Assistant to the President on Administration. The President gave the go-ahead to the appointment of Dr Kamal Abdurrahman Muhammad as Special Assistant to the President on Health and Personal Physician, all in the Office of the First Lady. This was contained in a statement made available to DAILY POST by Suleiman Haruna, Director of Information
to First Lady of Nigeria. President Buhari had earlier on Wednesday swore-in 43 Ministers who are expected to work with him within the next four years of his second and last term administration.  Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.